<br>
- a group invisible spell, a group levitation spell, a group see-invisible spell, a group ultravision spell. give wizards some spells that actually help the group directly. i'm thinking give it to them a spell level or two after they recieve the single target version.<br>
<br>
- a group harvest spell. i thinking this would be a 44ish level spell that would cost a bit of mana and deal out mana to everyone in the group. of course, it would have a long recast time.<br>
<br>
- a freeze spell. a high mana cost, stun only spell of considerable longer duration stun than most stuns. of course its an ice spell and would be resistable.<br>
<br>
- either make damage absorption &quot;skins&quot; castable on others or some new versions of these that we can cast on other people.<br>
<br>
- either make magic resistance buffs better so that it actually makes it difficult for Mobs to DD the masters of DD (a wizard Mob of the same level will resist a player's spell far more often than a player will resist a Mob spell, why does this happen?)or let us cast these on other people and stack with other resistance buffs. <br>
<br>
- bind physical spell. an anti-summon, anti-flux, anti-port/evac, anti-gate, anti-blink. a spell that can't be canceled and has good points and drawbacks. there are many ways this could be implemented and fine-tuned in test to make it work without affecting the game.<br>
<br>
Make wizards more interesting characters:<br>
<br>
- a blind spell. we can summon light stones and halos, and we can call down giant bolts of lightning to smite our foes, surely we can set off a small flash in the face of our enemies to blind them.<br>
<br>
- a second specialization skill. let wizards choose to furthur specialize their characters in fire, ice, lightning, or force forms of DD.<br>
<br>
- cast shielding spells on tailored items and player crafted armor to raise AC<br>
<br>
- allow wizards to recharge charged items. this could be a skill or a spell or something, obviously this wouldn't be an easy thing to do.<br>
<br>
- more quests that use or require identify. this is a spell that is greatly under-used and could make wizards feel more wanted (and bards, etc.)<br>
<br>
Dalatha <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uthesprawl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>thesprawl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/01 3:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wow... some</span><hr size=1> Some of those ideas were pretty crazy and don't really make us much better at dealing damage, but they were interesting at least. I think an ice based stun that sorta froze the mob in place would be nice, and maybe it could reduce their resistance to fire based spells while it stuck(anyone read the info hax0red from the spdat file that said the new Velium Chill spell turns something into an ice elemental of some sort?). I just have a feeling that if verant were to implement some of those things (group invis/see invis, skins castable on others, etc.) they wouldn't be for wizards (or wouldn't be for ONLY wizards)<br>
<br>
I think we need an OFFENSIVE version of the damage shield. Something that would even just do like 3-5 damage per hit at level 34 would be incredibly useful (maybe O'Keils Flickering Flame was meant to be this way originally?)<br>
<br>
Mages and all the other classes have the DEFENSE covered, but we're all about offense aren't we?<br>
We already have the knowledge to make a damage shield work, i'm sure al'kabor could do some tweaking and possibly make something like this workable (well maybe I'm not sure...)<br>
<br>
I know they promised enchanters that they would get a weapon enchantment thing, but enchanters don't have a single fire or ice spell so I can't see their 'enchanted weapons' being that incredible. Maybe they could give necros/shaman a poison based version of this offensive-type damage shield too, just as long as they don't give them better ones =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usealrin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sealrin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/01 3:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: = Making wizards more group friendly =</span><hr size=1> Well I always thaught wizards were there to do great damage and tanks were there to take it.  But now theyve givein tanks the power to do way more damage then us and increased their ability to take it. And they call this class balanceing?<br>
<br>
One thing I would like to see is us being able to actually do more damage than a rogue or warrior and such again, the way it should be <p><img src=http://sealrin.tripod.com/coollogo_com.12918557_26477.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubrinnyale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brinnyale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/01 9:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: = Making wizards more group friendly =</span><hr size=1> I have to say, although I know it will never happen, I really like the idea of group harvest.<br>
<br>
Brinnyale Rhyn<br>
53 Wizard of Bristlebane <p>Brinnyale Rhyn
level 52 Wizard of the Bristlebane Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usorasil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sorasil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 438<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/12/01 7:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: = Making wizards more group friendly =</span><hr size=1> The key to making wizards group friendly is to make us better at what the game is all about. DAMAGE.<br>
<br>
If we can regain a meaningfull damage mastery at our DD spells that outweights our weaknesses and lack of utility and that rival the damage dealing of a rogue and warrior  while the manaregeneration rate is increased SIGNIFICANTLY to eliminate downtime THEN we are groupfriendly. <p>Sorasil Lorewind <BR>
60th Level Sorcerer Of Guild Paradigm <BR>
Solusek Ro </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/12/01 9:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ah, Sorasil...</span><hr size=1> The voice of reason comes back... hehehe...  Haven't seen a post by you in awhle Sor.  Anyway, you're absolutely correct.  Help us to regain our damage dealing supremisy, and groups will want us.  I think some of the initial ideas on this thread are VERY creative and not at all unjustifyable.  Will they be implimented?  Nah.  But nice to think about.<br>
<br>
Wizards(as defined by Verant) - Masters of DD.<br>
<br>
Wizards(as difined by REALITY) - The only pawn in a group related game without one single solitary group utility that is not 100% replacable.  And on a side note, does respectable DD but by NO means, the master.<br>
<br>
And no, you can't say that about necros, mages, druids, which are the classes most people say... &quot;They have it just as bad as wizards.&quot;  If you look at the facts, it isn't even close.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalatha>Dalatha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/13/01 4:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Problem is...</span><hr size=1> About masters of DD:<br>
<br>
the problem is that if VI made us the masters of DD like they say we are, then we'd be able to solo too easily for the likes of VI. <br>
<br>
to make us group wanted by making DD better, they'd have to make our damage comparable to that of a warrior who doesn't have to worry about running out of mana and doesn't have to worry about resists and doesn't have to worry about the monster coming over to kill him in a few hits. this is not damage comparable to just one kill; we can easily out damage a warrior by wasting all our mana. it's about the whole group dynamic. <br>
<br>
About group dynamic (non-raid grouping):<br>
<br>
when we sit on our asses getting mana, tanks are doing fighting and buffs remind us of the fact that the other casters are still there. wizards are a low show class unless we're using all our mana to wipe something out or using our AoE spells. using up mana means we have to tell the group we're oom in which case they're angry at us for either making them wait on us, or angry that we're sitting there getting exp while they continue to fight. if we use our AoE in a group situation, we just tend to die (and that's no good). (please note that this is a generalization and differs at different levels with different spells)<br>
<br>
we rarely show to a group that we're really useful and we don't really do comparable damage to tanks in a non-stop pulling situation. <br>
<br>
Dalatha (i still love being a wizard but it distrubs me to hear people say there is balance where there isn't) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspace78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>space78</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/13/01 1:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Problem is...</span><hr size=1> first of all, and i cant say this enough obviously, WE ARE NOT A BUFFING CLASS.<br>
group spells, bah to hell with em, i dont want em, dont need em. those are covered by other classes. i like the idea of recharging items, but thats really an enchanter deal not a wizards. i like the freeze idea quite a bit though, would seem very useful and would help in crowd control.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uammeroutcaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ammer Outcaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/13/01 8:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Problem is...</span><hr size=1> Read my mind Space, we do nut buff and at most times glad I can't. We take care of ourselves, that's why we have clerics and the whole 9 yards. Plus, we wouldn't want to imbalance the Wizard class with other classes roflmao. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalatha>Dalatha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/15/01 5:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> more ideas for wizards</span><hr size=1> i got this idea as a result from my posts on another forum:<br>
<br>
how about a spell that say fires off 6 or so shots, will all shots landing at practically the same time. the thing is, if the 4th shot kills the mob then shots 5 and 6 don't go off and we don't have to pay the mana for those.<br>
<br>
i'm hoping this could help us save mana and make us more useful in a one-pull-at-a-time group. comments? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uexodia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Exodia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/22/01 7:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: more ideas for wizards</span><hr size=1> guys..you might fire me...but i am a necro..here..WHY A GROUP HARVEST..then its unbalanced...BUT..i think that you should get mana on your spells..as in..you cast..lets say ice comet...costs 400mana right? then if its full dmg you get 100mana back if its resisted 50 and if its totaly resisted none..how about that?no group harvest plz..or else they ll give group rez to cleric...and group sumon to necros..get real=) send me a tell in game for further discution=)<br>
